Casey (eBay Miniature Rescues) and Brent (Goobertown Hobbies) talk hobby and the importance of painting bravely.

The problem is that most people who start in this hobby quit within the first few years, and not because they donâ€™t enjoy the hobby. They become discouraged, they compare themselves, and their journey, to painters that have been doing it for years and year. They canâ€™t figure out a technique or donâ€™t think that they could ever paint â€œlike that,â€ and it creates a sense of unworthiness and fear. We are here to talk hobby, have some fun, and try and share our journeys in the hope that it will help you continue yours! After all, we are in this hobby to enjoy ourselves and have fun with friends. We want this podcast to be a place where you can find encouragement, discover ways to make your hobby fun, and most importantly Paint Bravely.
